        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 7:07PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 706 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Whitewater to 6 miles northeast of Hays.
Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Malta, Whitewater, Saco, Phillips, Sleeping Buffalo, Wagner,
Frenchman Reservoir, and Bowdoin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
